$TITLE ('Modem Device Driver Interface Routines')
$COMPACT OPTIMIZE(3) SET(ModemInterface) PAGEWIDTH (95)

ModemInterface: DO;

/*&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&
&	
&	Edit History: 	Refer to GRiDLink&PHonelinkLog~DataBase~
&
&	AUthors:		Monty Boyer
&					Rajendra Shah
&
&	This module implements all the calls to modem device driver under GRiD-OS.
&	This module is different between GRiD-OS and MS-DOS Phonelink.  
&
&	The MAIN routines are:
&
&		ModemInitialize		: set up connections and data structures.
&		ModemReset			: release connection, data structures.
&
&		ModemStart			: dial, establish data mode.
&		ModemStop			: disconect modem
&
&		ModemAttach			: 
&		ModemDetach			:
&
&		ModemDialPhone
&
&		ModemGetStatus		: check modem status & fifo
&		ModemReadBuffer		: read bytes from modem driver
&		ModemWriteBuffer	: write bytes to modem driver
&
&	The SUPPORT routines are (in alphabetical order):
&
&		EscHit
&		ModemLockAcquire
&		ModemLockRelease
&
&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&*/



$SAVE NOLIST

	/* My favourite literals */

$INCLUDE (``Incs`plm.inc~text~)

	/* Os Constants & Externals */

$SET (IncludeOsConstants)
$INCLUDE (``incs`Errors.inc~text~)

